Method Detail

write

public static void write(ReviewId reviewId,
                         ReviewIssueModel model,
                         java.io.File xmlFile)
                  throws java.io.IOException
Writes the content of all the code review data stored in the model into the XML file. Note that clients does not need to check if the specified file path (either directory or file) exists.

Clients should check if the passing File or/and ReviewIssueModel instance is not null. Otherwise the IllegalArgumentException is thrown.

Parameters:
reviewId - the review ID.
model - The model which contains the ReviewIssue instances.
xmlFile - The output XML file with absolute path.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if problems occur.

read

public static void read(ReviewId reviewId,
                        ReviewIssueModel model,
                        org.eclipse.core.resources.IFile[] iFiles)
Reads the xmlFile of the IFile instance to create ReviewIssue instances in the ReviewIssueModel instance. Note that the review file will be skipped if the problems occur on the reading process (e.g. XML file is not valid due to the file confliction).

Parameters:
reviewId - the review id.
model - The ReviewIssueModel instance to hold ReviewIssue instances.
iFiles - The array of IFile implementing class instance to hold file path.
